===Etymology 2===
Middle English ''[[gomme]]'' < Old French ''[[gome]]'' < Late Latin ''[[gumma]]'' < Latin ''[[gummi]]'' < Greek ''[[κόμμι]]'' < of Egyptian origin.

====Noun====
'''gum''' (''plural:'' '''gums''')
#any of various [[viscous]] or [[sticky]] [[substance]]s that are [[exude]]d by certain [[plant]]s
#any [[viscous]] or [[sticky]] [[substance]] resembling those that are [[exude]]d by certain [[plant]]s
#''(countable)'' a [[chewing gum]]

